messages.messageBody:
I gave Holly a dress last week that I've had since I was a teen.
It's very short, and she has worn it over jeans.

While I was out of town she took a photo of herself in it, and then
made it a kind of changing-colors show with photoshop.
http://sandradodd.blogspot.com/

It's not the expensive professional photoshop, it's Photoshop
Elements 2.0 (they're up to 4. or 5. now), and it cost less than $100
even when we got it a few years back.

If it weren't for MySpace, Holly probably wouldn't have learned to do
so many cool things with images and html.
Just playing around has given her lots of opportunity to learn things
she'll be able to use real-life.

Sandra
